RELATED: Two Zimbabwean witches crash land in Louis TrichardtGigaba has been lobbbying for removal of almost 200 000 Zimbabweans from Zimbabwe Special Permit so that they apply for the mainstream work permit. This might result in deportation of 200 000. The ZSP, by its nature, is a ministerial discretionary permit that s why we don t call it a visa. It s given to categories of people on the basis of special circumstances. It cannot qualify for permanent residence or even naturalisation afterwards. It is offered and it must lapse, Gigaba said.&nbsp;